    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uniform_dist function parameter type mismatch\n\n### Summary\nThe `uniform_dist` function was declared to take `int` parameters but was being called with floating-point values throughout the codebase. This caused incorrect behavior as floating-point arguments were truncated to integers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/MATH/oml.c`: Changed function signature from `uniform_dist(int min, int max)` to `uniform_dist(double min, double max)`\n- `openair2/UTIL/MATH/oml.h`: Updated function declaration to match implementation\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, calls like `uniform_dist(0.4, 1.2)` would return values in the range [0, 1] instead of [0.4, 1.2] due to integer truncation of parameters. Similarly, `uniform_dist(0, 1)` would always return 0 since both parameters became 0 after truncation.\n\nThis affected multiple modules including OTG traffic generation where timing delays and state transition probabilities were not being calculated correctly.\n"
}